OL,3,CHome Office 'cut corners' and 'wasted'
OL,4,C#15m on asbestos-riddled migrant camp
OL,6,FThe Home Office spent #15 million
OL,7,Fbuying a derelict prison site to house
OL,8,Fmigrants which turned out to be too
OL,9,Fcontaminated with asbestos to be used,
OL,10,Faccording to Whitehall's spending
OL,11,Fwatchdog.
OL,13,FThe former government, which was under
OL,14,Fpolitical pressure to stop housing
OL,15,Fmigrants in hotels, cut corners and
OL,16,Foverpaid for the Northeye site in East
OL,17,FSussex in 2023, the National Audit
OL,18,FOffice (NAO) says in a report
OL,19,Fpublished on Friday.
